-- WPP to Pay Out $500 Million Bonuses, Sorrel Says in Telegraph
-- B y   A l e x   M o r a l e s
-- 2012-02-05T09:18:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-05/wpp-to-pay-out-500-million-bonuses-sorrel-says-in-telegraph.html
WPP Plc (WPP)  will pay out about $500
million in performance-based bonuses after a “record year” in
2011, Chief Executive Officer  Martin Sorrell  wrote in a
commentary piece in the Sunday Telegraph.  The payout represents about 20 percent of the advertising
company’s pre-bonus operating profits, Sorrell said. 